OL,3,CGuernsey loses over half of its
OL,4,Chedgerows with fences partly to blame
OL,6,FA Guernsey ecologist says it is a
OL,7,F"real shame" that the island's nature-
OL,8,Frich hedgerows are declining, after a
OL,9,Freport concluded 52% have been lost
OL,10,Fsince 1999.
OL,12,FCharlotte Burgoyne from Guernsey's
OL,13,FNature Commission explains that
OL,14,Ffindings from the State of Nature 2024
OL,15,FReport could mean natural habitats are
OL,16,Fshrinking for the island's wildlife.
