OL,3,CGuernsey loses over half of its
OL,4,Chedgerows with fences partly to blame
OL,6,FOn hedgerows, she adds: "They provide
OL,7,Fshelter for many species. They provide
OL,8,Fflowers for nuts and berries, nesting
OL,9,Fareas, and foraging habitats. Species
OL,10,Fwill also use them to commute between
OL,11,Fplaces, so they're great corridors
OL,12,Fconnecting up our more fragmented
OL,13,Fareas, and it's easier for species to
OL,14,Ftravel along them."
OL,16,FIncluded in those species are
OL,17,Fpollinators like bees, which help
OL,18,Fmaintain biodiversity.
