OL,3,CGuernsey loses over half of its
OL,4,Chedgerows with fences partly to blame
OL,6,F"The only true native evergreen is
OL,7,Fholly and that can be a really nice
OL,8,Fevergreen dense hedge, but in exposed
OL,9,Fareas in Guernsey, people tend to lean
OL,10,Fon the more hardy, evergreen hedges
OL,11,Fsuch as elaeagnus and griselinia that
OL,12,Fdo nothing for biodiversity really."
OL,14,FLocal landscaper Nick Russell adds: "I
OL,15,Fdon't think anybody would rip a hedge
OL,16,Fout that was healthy and put a fence
OL,17,Fin, but maybe they do. I mean, we have
OL,18,Fdone it in the past.
